{"name": "realerikrani-pysteptest", "metadata": {"name": "realerikrani-pysteptest", "version": "1.0.0", "classifiers": [], "home_page": null, "license": "Apache-2.0", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["pytest"], "summary": "Pytest marker @pytest.mark.pysteptest for sequential tests in a class", "upload_time": 1735333560}, "documentation": ["# pysteptest\n\nAfter installing via pip, use the `@pytest.mark.pysteptest` marker on a class\nfor example for system tests\nthat need to happen in a specific order one after another.\nWhen one test fails, then do not run the following ones.\n\n```py\n@pytest.mark.pysteptest\nclass TestTodos:\n    def test_it_creates_todo(self):\n        # ...\n\n    def test_it_reads_todo(self):\n        # ...\n\n    def test_it_deletes_todo(self):\n        # ...\n```\n\nThis incremental marker is created by changing the code of <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/blob/24e84f08f43216f95620135305cbebe9f646e433/doc/en/example/simple.rst#incremental-testing---test-steps>.\nSee pytest repo's MIT license, LICENSE_OF_PYTEST file, included in the repository of this pysteptest project.\n"], "modules": [{"name": "realerikrani.pysteptest", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "realerikrani.pysteptest.marker", "documentation": ["This code is based on the code from the pytest docs:", "https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/blob/24e84f08f43216f95620135305cbebe9f646e433/doc/en/example/simple.rst#incremental-testing---test-steps", "See LICENSE_OF_PYTEST file in https://github.com/realerikrani/pysteptest", "for the MIT license of pytest project."], "functions": [{"name": "realerikrani.pysteptest.marker.pytest_configure", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "config", "type": {"name": "Config", "xref": {"fqname": "_pytest.config.Config", "project": "pytest"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "None", "xref": {"fqname": "constants.None", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "realerikrani.pysteptest.marker.pytest_runtest_makereport", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "item", "type": {"name": "Item", "xref": {"fqname": "_pytest.nodes.Item", "project": "pytest"}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "call", "type": {"name": "pytest.CallInfo", "xref": {"fqname": "pytest.CallInfo", "project": "pytest"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "None", "xref": {"fqname": "constants.None", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Hook to record failed tests for incremental testing."]}, {"name": "realerikrani.pysteptest.marker.pytest_runtest_setup", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "item", "type": {"name": "Item", "xref": {"fqname": "_pytest.nodes.Item", "project": "pytest"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "None", "xref": {"fqname": "constants.None", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Hook to mark tests as expected to fail if a previous test failed."]}], "variables": [{"name": "realerikrani.pysteptest.marker.INCREMENTAL_MARKER", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "realerikrani.pysteptest.marker.incremental_tracker", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [{"name": "realerikrani.pysteptest.marker.IncrementalTestTracker", "bases": [], "methods": [{"name": "realerikrani.pysteptest.marker.IncrementalTestTracker.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": {"name": "Self", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Self", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "None", "xref": {"fqname": "constants.None", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "realerikrani.pysteptest.marker.IncrementalTestTracker._has_test_failed", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "call", "type":